@* Regression probe for stale auto-registrations (see ErrorContentTests): implements IBrouterRoute
   directly - so the router's component reference capture auto-registers it, and (unlike
   BrouterRouteBase) nothing unregisters it on dispose - and vetoes every deactivation. When an
   error boundary's render replaces this page, its registration must be dropped with it, or the
   disposed instance's lock would cancel every later navigation. *@

@using Bit.Brouter
@implements IBrouterRoute

<div data-testid="elock-page">elock</div>

@code {
    public ValueTask OnDeactivatingAsync(BrouterRouteDeactivatingContext context)
    {
        context.Cancel();
        return ValueTask.CompletedTask;
    }
}
